                           Scatter Plot
Correlation : Correlation is a statistical measure that shows the relationship between two numerical variables.It tells us whether 
              one variable changes when another variable changes.
Types of Correlation :
1. Positive Correlation (+1) : Both variables increase or decrease together.
                              Example: Experience ↑ → Salary ↑
2. Negative Correlation (-1) : One variable increases while the other decreases.
                              Example: Speed ↑ → Travel Time ↓
3. No Correlation (0) : There is no relationship between the variables.
                       Example: Shoe Size and Salary
Correlation Value Range : +1 → Perfect positive correlation
                           0 → No correlation
                          -1 → Perfect negative correlation
Distribution : Distribution describes how the values of a variable are spread across a dataset. It helps us understand 
                the shape, center, and spread of the data.
Common Plots Used : Histogram,
                    Box Plot,
                    Density Plot (KDE)



